03/08/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- US President George W. Bush reaffirmed Washington's support for Macedonia's democratic reforms and Euro-Atlantic integration bid, in a message sent to President Branko Crvenkovski to mark the Ilinden Uprising national holiday celebrated on Wednesday (2 August). According to a press release from Crvenkovski's office, Bush also praised the growing partnership with Skopje in the global fight against terrorism. (Vecer - 03/08/06; Makfax - 02/08/06)
